---
title: Sweet Chili Beef & Broccoli with Buttery White Rice
description: Craving a sweet and savory takeout–style stir-fry? This version features garlicky ground beef simmered in a sweet, savory, and spicy blend of soy glaze, ponzu, and Thai chili sauce. It’s tossed with tender sautéed broccoli, then spooned over fluffy rice and garnished with zingy scallion greens. The best part? It’s all ready in a quick 20 minutes!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66fc215c99e8e2a18bd71eb6-e96f0b70.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66fc215c99e8e2a18bd71eb6-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-beef-and-broccoli-66fc215c99e8e2a18bd71eb6
time required: 20 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 920 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 93 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place broccoli in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover tightly with plastic wrap; poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. (You'll finish the broccoli in Step 5.)

In a #large bowl{}, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3%minutes}.

Continue to cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is browned and cooked through, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

Carefully drain any excess grease from pan. Turn off heat; transfer beef to bowl with sauce. Tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef. Add broccoli. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer broccoli to bowl with beef and sauce; toss until thoroughly coated.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} until melted.

Divide rice between bowls; top with beef and broccoli. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve.